  "slug": "grill-salmon",
  "name": "How to Grill Salmon",
  "recipe_type": "drink",
  "brief_description": "Now that you\u2019ve got an idea of the health benefits, it\u2019s time to learn how to grill salmon. Fillets are best for grilling and can be seasoned with garlic powder, lemon juice, salt, pepper, olive oil, sesame oil and many other seasonings. You will need:",
  "cuisine": null,
  "instructions": [
    {
      "position": 1,
      "text": "Rinse, debone, season and wrap salmon fillets in foil."
    },
    {
      "position": 2,
      "text": "Set your electric or gas grill to medium-high heat. If using charcoal, burn coals until you can hover your hands over the heat for 4 seconds."
    },
    {
      "position": 3,
      "text": "Make sure the salmon is skin side down and cook for 10-15 minutes. Check to see if it is flaky and opaque. If you don\u2019t have aluminum foil, grease the cooking grate with a little oil before placing the fish."
    },
    {
      "position": 4,
      "text": "Serve."
    }
  ],
  "servings": 4,
